    "client_msg_id": "18175190-b721-4d6f-97d8-6f5f8d1e1f54",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "This looks definitely interesting!\n\nWhat exactly are the types in your graph? Just arbitrarily defined tags, or do they have implications for the structure of the graph?\n\nA practical issue I see with any form of types for data structures meant to be very general is the need for some form of type refactoring.  You will certainly end up with near-synonym types (you have \"video\" and \"movie\" for example), or data that would fit several types (an e-book presented together with an introductory video on a Web page is... which of the three?), so at some point you may want to redesign and unify your types as the graph grows. I haven't yet seen any system that does this well.",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1623397915.067900",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
